  "learn": {
    "heading": "What is a multiple?",
    "intro": "<p>A <strong>multiple</strong> of a number is what you get by skip-counting it: multiples of 3 are 3, 6, 9, 12, 15… A <strong>common multiple</strong> of two numbers shows up in both lists. The <strong>least common multiple (LCM)</strong> is the smallest one they share.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>Multiples of 4:</strong> 4, 8, 12, 16, 20… <strong>Multiples of 6:</strong> 6, 12, 18, 24… The first shared one is <strong>12</strong>, so LCM(4, 6) = 12.",
      "Tip: keep skip-counting both lists until a number appears in both."
    ]
  },
